view.name: Traffic Violations
view.description:
This dataset contains traffic violation information from all electronic traffic violations issued in the County.  Any information that can be used to uniquely identify the vehicle, the vehicle owner or the officer issuing the violation will not be published.

Update Frequency:  Daily

columns.name: Date Of Stop
columns.description: Date of the traffic violation.

columns.name: Time Of Stop
columns.description: Time of the traffic violation.

columns.name: Agency
columns.description: Agency issuing the traffic violation.  (Example: MCP is Montgomery County Police)

columns.name: SubAgency
columns.description:
Court code representing the district of assignment of the officer. 
R15 = 1st district, Rockville
B15 = 2nd district, Bethesda
SS15 = 3rd district, Silver Spring
WG15 = 4th district, Wheaton
G15 = 5th district, Germantown
M15 = 6th district, Gaithersburg / Montgomery Village
HQ15 = Headquarters and Special Operations

columns.name: Description
columns.description: Text description of the specific charge.

columns.description: If traffic violation involved an accident.

columns.description: If traffic violation involved Property Damage.

columns.name: Fatal

columns.description: If driver holds a Commercial Drivers License.

columns.name: HAZMAT

columns.name: Commercial Vehicle
columns.description: If the vehicle committing the traffic violation is a commercial vehicle.

columns.description: If the traffic violation included an alcohol related

columns.name: Work Zone
columns.description: If the traffic violation was in a work zone.

columns.name: State
columns.description: State issuing the vehicle registration.

columns.name: VehicleType
columns.description: Type of vehicle (Examples: Automobile, Station Wagon, Heavy Duty Truck, etc.)

columns.name: Year
columns.description: Year vehicle was made.

columns.name: Make
columns.description: Manufacturer of the vehicle (Examples: Ford, Chevy, Honda, Toyota, etc.)

columns.name: Model
columns.description: Model of the vehicle.

columns.name: Color
columns.description: Color of the vehicle.

columns.name: Violation Type
columns.description: Violation type.  (Examples: Warning, Citation, SERO)

columns.name: Charge
columns.description: Numeric code for the specific charge.

columns.name: Article
columns.description: Article of State Law.  (TA = Transportation Article, MR = Maryland Rules)

columns.name: Contributed To Accident
columns.description: If the traffic violation was a contributing factor in an accident.

columns.name: Race
columns.description: Race of the driver.  (Example: Asian, Black, White, Other, etc.)

columns.name: Gender
columns.description: Gender of the driver (F = Female, M = Male)

columns.name: Driver City
columns.description: City of the driver’s home address.

columns.name: Driver State
columns.description: State of the driver’s home address.

columns.name: DL State
columns.description: State issuing the Driver’s License.

columns.name: Arrest Type
columns.description: Type of Arrest (A = Marked, B = Unmarked, etc.)

columns.name: Geolocation
